body: Actually, I have a question for @svarnau, who told me the answer a while ago: Somehow I thought there were more places where the version number is stored. Is this the only place where we need a change? Maybe no longer, since it looks like DCS also changed their pom.xml file to get the version from an environment variable?

For hive ddl operations, we need a hive_admin kind of traf privilege. 
If a user has that privilege, then they should be allowed to do hive DDL operations.
This would be relevant for explicit hive ddl, or for temp table ddl (as Hans mentioned)
or future support for volatile tables in hive.
Hive ddl privilege support need to be added.

For the first phase, only ddl operations are supported. We would extend for
some dml operations in a subsequent checkin.

I believe all of the other places are fixed to use TRAFODION_VER.  
I may need to re-visit the ambari plugin so that it is configured to handle 2.1 and 2.2, but that is a downstream task.

This seems like it's ready for merging. @svarnau were you concerened about the RH in the package name ? Do you want to ccreate a separate JIRA to look into the package name ?

The sqf/Makefile does:
OS_TYPE = RH
OS_MAJOR ?=  $(shell lsb_release -rs | cut -f1 -d.)
PKG_TYPE="server-$(TRAFODION_VER)-${OS_TYPE}${OS_MAJOR}-${P_TYPE}-incubating"

I guess if the build system does not have lsb_release command installed, it might come out blank instead of "6".  But the intent is that the name have RH6 or RH7, not just RH.
I see the same issue when I build on a VM. So is there a new RPM we need to add tot he list of needed rpms before a build ?

Actually I see lsb_release is present on the VM but the output of the package is still RH -
[centos@sandhya-amb-2 distribution]$ lsb_release -rs
6.7
[centos@sandhya-amb-2 distribution]$ lsb_release -rs | cut -f1 -d.
6

--
These are the package names : 
apache-trafodion_clients-2.1.0-RH-x86_64-debug.tar.gz
apache-trafodion_installer-2.1.0-incubating.tar.gz
apache-trafodion_pyinstaller-2.1.0-incubating.tar.gz
apache-trafodion-regress.tgz
apache-trafodion_server-2.1.0-RH-x86_64-debug.tar.gz

Interesting. OS_MAJOR is being set with ?=, which means it could be inheriting it from an environment variable.  Otherwise, I don't understand why OS_MAJOR is not being set for some people.  It works in my dev environment and in jenkins.
My fresh build on a dev workstation did have the correct RH6 package name. It's only on a openstack VM I saw this. So the setting of OS_MAJOR seems to not be deterministic.
Eitherway, we shoudl probably get this documentation change merged  in ?
Agreed, this is a tangent and a minor issue for the doc.
